Context: The text provides information on how to register for courses at George Brown College, request proof of enrolment, Education Verifications Request, Registered Education Savings Plan (RESP) forms, Canadian Pension Plan (CPP) forms, and the process to withdraw from courses for both full-time and part-time domestic students. The contact information provided includes a phone number (416-415-2000), TTY number (1-877-515-5559), email address (ask.george@georgebrown.ca), and social media hub. It is important to note that the information contained in the website is subject to change without notice, and students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
